│ was created with invalid operands.\n\n2. Analyzing `opt`'s Log: The         │
│ backtrace shows that the issue originates in `tryToFoldLiveIns` function in │
│ VPlanTransforms.cpp at line 986, where `Folder.FoldExtractElement(Ops[0],   │
│ Ops[1])` is called. The debugger reveals that Ops[0] is i32 0 (integer      │
│ type) and Ops[1] is i32 1 (integer type), but `FoldExtractElement` expects  │
│ the first operand to be a vector type.\n\n3. Root Cause Analysis: The       │
│ problem is that `tryToFoldLiveIns` doesn't validate that the operands for   │
│ ExtractElement are appropriate before calling `FoldExtractElement`.         │
