│ from the PHI node in the original IR. The PHI node `%phi = phi i64 [ %rem,  │
│ %else ], [ 0, %loop ]` gets truncated to i32 and then used in a context     │
│ where vectorization assumes it should be part of a vector operation, but    │
│ the live-in folding logic doesn't check the type validity.\n\n4. Proposed   │
│ Edit Point(s): The fix should be in `tryToFoldLiveIns` function to add a    │
│ type check before attempting to fold ExtractElement instructions. We need   │
│ to ensure that the first operand is actually a vector type before calling   │
│ `FoldExtractElement`.\n\n5. Conclusion: By adding a guard condition in      │
│ `tryToFoldLiveIns` to verify that the first operand of an ExtractElement    │
